<br>
Level 45, do you recall that wonderfull level? Let me tell you a little story.<br>
<br>
Back then the people know who the xp leaders were. It was a fun game.<br>
I worked non-stop for 16 hours a day trying to get OUT of level 45. At that time<br>
there were VERY few places where you could go, Guk Vox FireGiants beetles<br>
so you kept running into the same people. I was unable to aquire a cleric sufficient<br>
for my needs. So I was pretty much limited to Guk and picking off frogs.<br>
I didnt have a pet shaman you see. But I make progress slowly painfully.<br>
I see Remdar Tzzird and Teuvas in zone, I assumed working Frenzied. No one<br>
else was down there. Now I had not spoken to any of them since level 25?<br>
We had had a dissagreement while doing HK you see. Remdar had long since <br>
become level 50, I had no idea what he had been doing, but I digress.<br>
I had realized that the xp issue (the cause of the fight) was no longer important.<br>
So why bear a grudge? So I sent old Remdar a tell, telling him that he had been right and me wrong. After a virtual conversation I certainly felt better. I dont<br>
have any idea what he thought. After Seven long days of haunting Lguk i finnaly<br>
broke 45 to 46. I was overjoyed I was happy. As was my habit when happy<br>
I went by the frog with GB on the way out. It is easy for a monk to solo this guy<br>
forever unaided. There were three guys I had never seen before. I mean NEVER.<br>
One of them was a Paladin named Lucas. Well they greeted my arrival with the same enthusiam as Cops at a kegger. I backed off, I had a policy you see,<br>
always yield to anyone who has a legitimate need for the item. But I did note the levels. The next day I swing thru again, they are still there but one level higher,<br>
next day I swing thru again, same thing but one level higher. Sometimes there were<br>
only two of them. After a week of this amazing progress I sent Leiran a tell.<br>
'Who the hell is Lucas?'<br>
I can hear all you guys laughing. But I really didnt know. I wont bore you with a rundown on Lucas but lets say that one of the few things DK and I agreed on was Lucas. I verified the guy was exploiting/cheating/whatever you want to call it.<br>
Nada. Verant did nothing. NOTHING. <br>
<br>
Now maybe I am not the greatest monk in the world but I was proud of my progress. These cheap bastards just invalidated all my work. What was there to be proud of? And they walked all over everyone getting there. I saw red, I seriously considered training their sorry asses to hell. I gnashed my teeth, I was ENRAGED.<br>
<br>
But I left after saying 'How does one get 7 levels in 7 days Lucas?'<br>
<br>
That was when I realized how pervasive the exploitation problem was on Erollis Marr. <br>
<br>
I decided I would fight it. I didnt realize who exactly I would be fighting.<br>
People dont like it when you arrive and a GM shows up 20 min later.<br>
They tend to think you had something to do with it.<br>
<br>
Then of course we have simple abusive players. Lucas was both.<br>
<br>
I dont like cheaters Birren. That is why I never played on UO. Some 14yearold<br>
punk with a hack kills you. wow.<br>
Cheaters suck. I also dont like PK elitists, in general I dont like abusive players.<br>
People who hog camps, usurp zones, tell me to get lost, people who try to force me to leave.  I can and do fight them, as best I can. Most of them are gone<br>
now. They left for the vaporware called Shadowbane. But not all.<br>
<br>
Do you realize that all a person would have to do is play nice, and I would walk away? But its too much to ask, on Erollis Marr.<br>
